If outward Proſperity be not good for bad Men, then the Force of the Objection vaniſhes, but the Caſe is realy thus; Proſperity is ſo far from being good to them, that it is the very reverſe, it is like a ſick Patients uſing ſuch ſtrong Dyet as tends to make his diſeaſe incurable; Proſperity flatters their Pride, and is fuel to their Luxury; by it they are fattened for the Day of Slaughter; 
               we ought not to Lament, Iſidore.
thoſe who ſmart when they offend, but thoſe who go on in ſin unpuniſhed.
